# TypeScript Standards

## Types

- No `any` types — use `unknown` and narrow, or define proper interfaces
- Define interfaces for all API response shapes in `frontend/lib/api.ts`
- `BlockConfig` interface is the canonical type for all dashboard blocks

## Naming

- `PascalCase` for components, interfaces, and types
- `camelCase` for variables, functions, and props
- Files: `PascalCase.tsx` for components, `camelCase.ts` for utilities

## Components

- All components are functional — no class components
- Use Tremor components before building custom ones
- If a Tremor component exists for the use case, use it
- No inline styles — Tailwind classes only
- Mark `"use client"` only when the component requires browser APIs or event handlers
- Prefer Server Components where possible

## API calls

- All API fetch calls go in `frontend/lib/api.ts` — never inline in components
- Components receive data as props or via a dedicated hook
- No hardcoded API URLs in components — use `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` env var

## Block system

- Every visual dashboard element must use the `BlockConfig` + `BlockRenderer` pattern
- Never build one-off chart components — use `LineChartBlock`, `BarChartBlock`, etc.
- Chart data always flows through the generic `/api/repos/{id}/data` endpoint

## Import order

1. React / Next.js
2. Tremor components
3. Other third-party
4. Local components
5. Local lib/utils
6. Types
